chkala]].<ref name=career>{{FootballFacts.ru|22220-mamaev-eldar-kamilevich}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mamayev, Eldar}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Russian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:FC Anzhi Makhachkala players]]\n[[Category:FC Ural Yekaterinburg players]]\n[[Category:FC Nizhny Novgorod players]]\n[[Category:FC Khimki players]]\n[[Category:FC Sakhalin Yuzhno-Sakhalinsk players]]\n[[Category:Russian Premier League players]]\n[[Category:FC Sever Murmansk players]]\n\n\n{{Russia-footy-midfielder-1985-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Zyxw", "label": "safe", "comment": "update FootballFacts.ru template, misc formatting", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eldar_Mamayev"}
{"title_page": "Sini\u0161a Stevanovi\u0107", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Sini\u0161a Stevanovi\u0107\n| image          = Sini\u0161a Stevanovi\u0107.jpg\n| image_size     = 200px\n| caption        = Stevanovi\u0107 playing for [[FK Novi Pazar|Novi Pazar]] in 2015\n| fullname       = Sini\u0161a Stevanovi\u0107\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1989|01|12|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Belgrade]], [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|SFR Yugoslavia]]\n| height         = {{Height|m=1.76}}\n| position       = [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Right-back]]\n| currentclub    = [[FK \u017deljezni\u010dar Sarajevo|\u017deljezni\u010dar]]\n| clubnumber     = 2\n| youthyears1    = 2004\u20132007\n| youthclubs1    = [[FK Partizan|Partizan]]\n| years1         = 2007\u20132009\n| clubs1         = [[FK Teleoptik|Teleoptik]]\n| caps1          = 26\n| goals1         = 0\n| years2         = 2009\u20132010\n| clubs2         = [[FK Partizan|Partizan]]\n| caps2          = 11\n| goals2         = 0\n| years3         = 2010\n| clubs3         = \u2192 [[FK Spartak Subotica|Spartak Subotica]] (loan)\n| caps3          = 15\n| goals3         = 0\n| years4         = 2010\u20132013\n| clubs4         = [[FK Spartak Subotica|Spartak Subotica]]\n| caps4          = 49\n| goals4         = 1\n| years5         = 2014\u20132016\n| clubs5         = [[FK Novi Pazar|Novi Pazar]]\n| caps5          = 32\n| goals5         = 0\n| years6         = 2016\u2013\n| clubs6         = [[FK \u017deljezni\u010dar Sarajevo|\u017deljezni\u010dar]]\n| caps6          = 96\n| goals6         = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2009\u20132010\n| nationalteam1  = [[Serbia national under-21 football team|Serbia U21]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 10\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| pcupdate       = 8 March 2020\n| ntupdate       =\n}}\n'''Sini\u0161a Stevanovi\u0107''' ([[Serbian Cyrillic alphabet|Serbian Cyrillic]]: \u0421\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0448\u0430 \u0421\u0442\u0435\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u045b; born 12 January 1989) is a Serbian professional [[Football player|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right-back]] for [[Premier League of Bosnia and Herzegovina|Bosnian Premier League]] club [[FK \u017deljezni\u010dar Sarajevo|\u017deljezni\u010dar]].\n\n==Club career==\nA product of [[FK Partizan|Partizan]]'s youth system, Stevanovi\u0107 made his senior team debut with their affiliated club [[FK Teleoptik|Teleoptik]], before being promoted to Partizan's first team in the summer of 2009.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://staraarhiva.partizan.rs/vest.php?Jezik=sr&IDV=456&akcija=show&prikaz1=2009&prikaz2=6&sec=2 | title=U Partizan su do\u0161li tiho... | language=Serbian | publisher=partizan.rs | date=27 June 2009 | accessdate=28 May 2015}}</ref> He was loaned to [[FK Spartak Subotica|Spartak Subotica]] in January 2010,<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://staraarhiva.partizan.rs/vest.php?Jezik=sr&IDV=90&akcija=show&prikaz1=2010&prikaz2=1&sec=2 | title=Stevanovi\u0107 u Spartaku | language=Serbian | publisher=partizan.rs | date=28 January 2010 | accessdate=28 May 2015}}</ref> before signing a permanent contract with the club in the summer of 2010.\n\nIn January 2014, Stevanovi\u0107 moved to another [[Serbian SuperLiga|Superliga]] club [[FK Novi Pazar|Novi Pazar]].\n\nIn the 2016 winter transfer window, Stevanovi\u0107 left Novi Pazar and moved to [[Premier League of Bosnia and Herzegovina|Bosnian Premier League]] club [[FK \u017deljezni\u010dar Sarajevo|\u017deljezni\u010dar]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fkzeljeznicar.ba/sinisa-stevanovic-novi-fudbaler-zeljeznicara/17826/|title=Sini\u0161a Stevanovi\u0107 novi fudbaler \u017deljezni\u010dara|language=Bosnian|publisher=fkzeljeznicar.ba|date=25 December 2015|accessdate=22 January 2016}}</ref> He won his first trophy with \u017deljezni\u010dar in the [[2017\u201318 FK \u017deljezni\u010dar season|2017\u201318]] season, the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina Football Cup|Bosnian Cup]].<ref>[https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/zeljeznicar-osvojio-kup-bosne-i-hercegovine/276194 \u017deljezni\u010dar osvojio Kup Bosne i Hercegovine!] at sportsport.ba, 9 May 2018</ref> On 24 June 2019, Stevanovi\u0107 extended his contract with \u017deljezni\u010dar, which is due to keep him at the club until the summer of 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/stevanovic-produzio-vjernost-fk-zeljeznicar/323718|title=Stevanovi\u0107 produ\u017eio vjernost FK \u017deljezni\u010dar!|date=24 June 2019|accessdate=24 June 2019|language=Bosnian|author=A. \u010cau\u0161evi\u0107|publisher=sportsport.ba}}</ref> On 27 July 2019, in a 0\u20132 away league win against [[FK Mladost Doboj Kakanj|Mladost Doboj Kakanj]], he made his 100th appearance for \u017deljezni\u010dar.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/stevanovic-nakon-100-nastupa-za-fk-zeljeznicar-neki-od-nas-se-jos-nisu-oporavili-od-te-utakmice/327694|title=Stevanovi\u0107 nakon 100. nastupa za FK \u017deljezni\u010dar: \"Neki od nas se jo\u0161 nisu oporavili od te utakmice\"|date=27 July 2019|accessdate=29 July 2019|language=Bosnian|author=A. \u010cau\u0161evi\u0107|publisher=sportsport.ba}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.klix.ba/sport/nogomet/zeljeznicar-rutinski-slavio-u-gostima-kod-mladosti-i-upisao-prvu-pobjedu-ove-sezone/190727079|title=\u017deljezni\u010dar rutinski slavio u gostima kod Mladosti i upisao prvu pobjedu ove sezone|date=27 July 2019|accessdate=27 July 2019|language=Bosnian|author=E.B.|publisher=Klix.ba}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nBetween 2009 and 2010, Stevanovi\u0107 represented [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]] at [[Serbia national under-21 football team|under-21 level]], making nine appearances.\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 8 March 2020.}}<ref name=\"soccerway\">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/sinisa-stevanovic/84033/|title=S. Stevanovi\u0107: Summary|accessdate=8 March 2020|language=English|website=Soccerway|publisher=Perform Group}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:95%\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!rowspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"|[[FK Partizan|Partizan]] \n|[[2009\u201310 Serbian SuperLiga|2009\u201310]]\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[Serbian SuperLiga]] \n||11||0||2||0||8||0||21||0\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[FK Spartak Subotica|Spartak Subotica]]\n|[[2009\u201310 Serbian SuperLiga|2009\u201310]] \n||15||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2013||15||0\n|-\n|[[2010\u201311 Serbian SuperLiga|2010\u201311]]||24||0||3||0||3||0||30||0\n|-\n|[[2011\u201312 Serbian SuperLiga|2011\u201312]]||16||1||2||0||colspan=2|\u2013||18||1\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Serbian SuperLiga|2012\u201313]]||2||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2013||2||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!57!!1!!5!!0!!3!!0!!65!!1\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[FK Novi Pazar|Novi Pazar]]\n|[[2012\u201313 Serbian SuperLiga|2012\u201313]]\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Serbian SuperLiga]] \n||5||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2013||5||0\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 Serbian SuperLiga|2013\u201314]]\n|7||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2013||7||0\n|-\n|[[2014\u201315 Serbian SuperLiga|2014\u201315]]\n||11||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2013||11||0\n|-\n|[[2015\u201316 Serbian SuperLiga|2015\u201316]]\n|16||0||1||0||colspan=2|\u2013||17||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!39!!0!!1!!0!!0!!0!!40!!0\n|-\n|rowspan=6|[[FK \u017deljezni\u010dar Sarajevo|\u017deljezni\u010dar]]\n|[[2015\u201316 FK \u017deljezni\u010dar season|2015\u201316]]\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[Premier League of Bosnia and Herzegovina|Bosnian Premier League]]\n|10||0||4||0||colspan=2|\u2013||14||0\n|-\n|[[2016\u201317 FK \u017deljezni\u010dar season|2016\u201317]]\n|26||0||4||0||colspan=2|\u2013||30||0\n|-\n|[[2017\u201318 FK \u017deljezni\u010dar season|2017\u201318]]\n|19||0||